		"Pelvic health assessment to understand your symptoms",
		"Personalised pelvic floor muscle training",
		"Advice on bladder and bowel habits",
		"Exercises for strength, control, and coordination",
		"Support with returning to exercise safely",
		"Education and reassurance throughout recovery",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Women with pelvic floor symptoms affecting daily comfort or confidence",
		"Mums-to-be and postnatal women managing pelvic pain or abdominal separation",
		"Women with bladder urgency, frequency or leaking",
		"Patients experiencing pain during or after sex",
		"Active women returning to exercise after pregnancy or surgery",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "Do I need an internal examination?", a: "No. it\\'s always your choice. We can still assess and treat many issues without it." },
		{ q: "Is leaking after childbirth normal?", a: "It\\'s common, but not something you have to live with. Treatment can make a big difference." },
		{ q: "How many sessions will I need?", a: "It varies, but many people start to see improvement within a few sessions." },
		{ q: "Can you help with pain during sex?", a: "Yes. this is something we treat regularly, in a sensitive and supportive way." },
		{ q: "Can I attend during menstruation?", a: "Yes. If you\\'d prefer, we can adjust the session to suit your comfort." },
	]}
/>
